(1)
Washington Street, north from Tillary (right) to Concord (left) Streets, showing a general view across the B.M.T. yards, as seen from the Hotel Tour-aine. Yards shown, are on the west side of Washington Street.

December 16, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, a more extensive view, showing Gunnison Square in the foreground under construction.

P. L. Sperr.
